On July 16, 1971, the 100,000th car of the VAZ brand was produced. On January 10, 1972, the State Commission signed an act on the acceptance into operation of the second stage of the Volga Automobile Plant with a capacity of 220 thousand cars per year. Officially, the plant was accepted by the State Commission with a rating of "excellent" 22 December 1973 - after the release of the millionth car; by decree of the Presidium of the USSR Armed Forces, the Volga Automobile Plant was awarded the Order of the Red Banner of Labor [15]. For the architecture of the Volga Automobile Plant complex in 1977, the USSR State Prize in Literature, Art and Architecture was awarded [2]. was 660 thousand cars a year, by the beginning of the 1990s, the capacity reached 740 thousand.